          "lessons": [
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 1,
              "weekLabel": "Week 1",
              "sequence": 1,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 1",
              "title": "40m Econ/Civics: Grade 11 (Canada) - Lesson 1",
              "body": "⍞ Materials: The Art of Asking Better Questions, Journal or Notebook, Bible\n\n➜ READ\nIntro-Ch.1, p.3-25\n\n➜ REFLECT\nThink about the individuals that you interact with on a daily basis. Identify someone that askes good questions and ask that person what motivstes him or her to ask good questions..",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recR08hYlEFiOfYmj&6J82c=recDW4MiNLh89T5N0"
            },
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 2,
              "weekLabel": "Week 2",
              "sequence": 2,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 2",
              "title": "40m Econ/Civics: Grade 11 (Canada) - Lesson 2",
              "body": "⍞ Materials: The Art of Asking Better Questions, Journal or Notebook, Bible\n\n➜ READ\nCh. 2, p.26-39\n\n➜ REVIEW & LIST\nReview the italicized questions throughout this chapter and list three questions in your journal or notebookthat were intriguing to you. Explain why.",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recR08hYlEFiOfYmj&6J82c=rec074wvFVu2EnhTE"
            },
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 3,
              "weekLabel": "Week 3",
              "sequence": 3,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 3",
              "title": "40m Econ/Civics: Grade 11 (Canada) - Lesson 3",
              "body": "⍞ Materials: The Art of Asking Better Questions, Journal or Notebook, Bible\n\n➜ READ\nCh. 3, p.40-57\n\n➜ LISTEN & Track\nDivide a piece of paper into four squares. Write one of the four levels of questions in each square. One day this week, listen for the four levels of questions being asked by those around you and track how many times you hear the four levels of questions throughout the day.",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recR08hYlEFiOfYmj&6J82c=recTrV2VHI4T7oorE"
            },
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 4,
              "weekLabel": "Week 4",
              "sequence": 4,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 4",
              "title": "40m Econ/Civics: Grade 11 (Canada) - Lesson 4",
              "body": "⍞ Materials: The Art of Asking Better Questions, Journal or Notebook, Bible\n\n➜ READ\nCh. 4, p.61-71\n\n➜ INTERVIEW\nIdentify one adult and one person your age to interview using David Brooks' questions listed on p.69. Give yourself plenty of time to interview each person. The goal is to get to know the person better, not simply to get through the questions.",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recR08hYlEFiOfYmj&6J82c=recW6yJMurTLtHKo3"
            },
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 5,
              "weekLabel": "Week 5",
              "sequence": 5,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 5",
              "title": "40m Econ/Civics: Grade 11 (Canada) - Lesson 5",
              "body": "⍞ Materials: The Art of Asking Better Questions, Journal or Notebook, Bible\n\n➜ READ\nCh.5-6, p.72-92\n\n➜ WRITE\nIn your own words, list and explain the six reasons Jesus asked questions.",
              "teacherNotes": "After you read ch.5-6, Review Resource 4: Fascinating Facts About The Questions Jesus Asked on p.181-185.",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recR08hYlEFiOfYmj&6J82c=recXcBa6stP2nJuhL"
            },
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 6,
              "weekLabel": "Week 6",
              "sequence": 6,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 6",
              "title": "40m Econ/Civics: Grade 11 (Canada) - Lesson 6",
              "body": "⍞ Materials: The Art of Asking Better Questions, Journal or Notebook, Bible\n\n➜ READ\nCh.7, p.93-101\n\n➜ REFLECT & ASK\nReflect on the questions you have regarding God, the Bible, and faith. Ask the members of your family what questions they have regarding God, the Bible, and faith. Identify the questions that you have in common and as a family, take steps towards answering those questions.",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recR08hYlEFiOfYmj&6J82c=recRynWRbUveZ5mLf"
            },
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 7,
              "weekLabel": "Week 7",
              "sequence": 7,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 7",
              "title": "40m Econ/Civics: Grade 11 (Canada) - Lesson 7",
              "body": "⍞ Materials: The Art of Asking Better Questions, Journal or Notebook, Bible\n\n➜ READ\nCh.8-9, p.105-123\n\n➜ INTERVIEW\nIdentify a person who is responsible for leading people and schedule a time to interview that person. Identify questions from ch. 8-9 (especially from p, 111 & 116) to ask during the interview. Reflect on your own leadership influence and ask yourself the questions on p. 111 & 116. If time permits, interview several leaders and compare their responses.",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recR08hYlEFiOfYmj&6J82c=recy0SpyXyDqvtw2C"
            },
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 8,
              "weekLabel": "Week 8",
              "sequence": 8,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 8",
              "title": "40m Econ/Civics: Grade 11 (Canada) - Lesson 8",
              "body": "⍞ Materials: The Art of Asking Better Questions, Journal or Notebook, Bible\n\n➜ READ\nCh.10, p.126-137\n\n➜ PLAN & IMPLEMENT\nDesignate a journal to be your Questions Journal. Reflect on the nine practices from ch. 9 and organize the journal accordingly. Do not be tempted to rush this assignment. The more time you spend creating a Questions Journal, the great likelihood you will see a transformation in how you ask questions.",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recR08hYlEFiOfYmj&6J82c=recB3V6fkHRmV3Wl6"
            },
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 9,
              "weekLabel": "Week 9",
              "sequence": 9,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 9",
              "title": "40m Econ/Civics: Grade 11 (Canada) - Lesson 9",
              "body": "⍞ Materials: The Art of Asking Better Questions, Journal or Notebook, Bible\n\n➜ READ\nCh.11, p. 138-150\n\n➜ PRACTICE\nIdentify a family member or friend to participate in a question-asking exercise with you. On p.147, read #6 \"Hold a questions-only conversation with others.\" Once you both understand the exercise, initiate the conversation and see how long the discussion lasts. Keep practicing until the exercise becomes more natural.",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recR08hYlEFiOfYmj&6J82c=recRHmdF2LDfRWYo8"
            },
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 10,
              "weekLabel": "Week 10",
              "sequence": 10,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 10",
              "title": "40m Econ/Civics: Grade 11 (Canada) - Lesson 10",
              "body": "⍞ Materials: The Art of Asking Better Questions, Journal or Notebook, Bible\n\n➜ READ\nCh.12-Conclusion, p.151-160\n\n➜ RECEIVE FEEDBACK\nIdentify two people that you interact with consistently and ask them to provide feedback on how you ask questions. Use the questions on p.152-153 to guide the conversation. The purpose of this exercise is to develop the skill of asking better questions. Do not be offended by the feedback you recieve. Embrace the feedback and develop action steps that will help you further develop the ability to ask great questions.",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recR08hYlEFiOfYmj&6J82c=recosDKQ7GfiCnmn3"
            },
            {
              "termNumber": 1,
              "termLabel": "Term 1",
              "weekNumber": 11,
              "weekLabel": "Week 11",
              "sequence": 11,
              "lessonLabel": "Lesson 11",
              "title": "40m Econ/Civics: Grade 11 (Canada) - Lesson 11",
              "body": "⍞ Materials: The Art of Asking Better Questions, Journal or Notebook, Bible\n\n➜ READ\nResource 2: Questions To Ask Ourselves, p.171-173\n\n➜ REFLECT & REVIEW\nReview the Self-Reflection Questions on p.171-173. Which questions are the most difficult to answer? What changes do you want to make in light of these questions.",
              "teacherNotes": "",
              "editUrl": "https://airtable.com/apphTWdjAdJEcAmoe/pago27hsdn3q8TtGK?XRKkD=recR08hYlEFiOfYmj&6J82c=recfZEGQ0UH6tgIIL"
            },
